data.title: Northrop Grumman cargo ship concludes three-month stay at space station
data.summary: A Northrop Grumman Cygnus cargo freighter departed the International Space Station Wednesday after delivering more than 7,800 pounds of equipment and experiments, heading for an extended mission with payloads to study fire behavior in microgravity and test a next-generation radio system.

data.title: NG-14 Cygnus departs ISS, kicks off busy year for Station crew
data.summary: After a period of over three months in which the spacecraft was berthed to the nadir (Earth-facing) port of the International Space Station’s Unity module, the 14th Northrop Grumman Cygnus spacecraft vacated the vicinity of the orbital outpost on Wednesday after being unberthed and released from the Space Station Remote Manipulator System (SSMRS), also known as Canadarm2.

data.title: NASA sets mid-January target for SLS hot fire test
